@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@next "Disclaimer"
 Introduction

One of the problems   of   MIDI    sequencing   software   packages  on the
Amiga platform  is  the  lack  of  multi-editing   tools  required  for the
production of professional quality MIDI  music..  Up  until   now,  Music-X
V2.0 only came bundled with 5 ARexx  macros for manipulating  MIDI data but
pointed the way to  the  possibilities  for  the  creation of further ARexx
macros as additional  Music-X  editing  tools..  We   have   attempted   to
improve  the effeciency  of  Music-X  by  producing  some  additional ARexx
macros for further maniplulating MIDI EVENT  data within the Music-X   V2.0
Sequencer  environment  for  a  whole   host  of  different  applications..
Hopefully,   these additional ARexx macros will make other Amiga MIDI musos
lives a little easier...

Some  of  the  ARexx macros  featured  here  function on ALL  or   SELECTED
EVENTS,   some  on  simply  NOTE  EVENTS   and  some  on  simply  MIDI  CTL
(Controller) EVENTS.. This AmigaGuide  document  contains  a list,  of each
ARexx macro followed by a detailed description of its intended usage.

See @{"ARexx Macro Descriptions" link "Macro Descriptions" 0}

This package also contains a detailed  selection of grabbed IFF screenshots
from within the  Music-X  V2.0  sequencer  software  which  act  as graphic
illustrations as an aid  to  understanding  how  each  of  the ARexx macros
function..
@endnode

